communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Public reports show that the robotic delivery company Starship is operating at your university: https://www.starship.xyz/starship-food-delivery-app/

Therefore, I hereby request the following records:

1) All agreements/contracts between the University Student Affairs, Starship, and/or Aramark regarding the use and policies of the Delivery Robots, or regarding Personal Delivery Devices.
2) All communication between the University Student Affairs and Starship regarding the Personal Delivery Devices/Delivery Robots. 
3) All communication between the University Student Affairs and Aramark regarding the Personal Delivery Devices/Delivery Robots. 

Please search between August 1, 2023 and the time this request is processed.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Skylar Ferguson

title: New construction permits in the last 2 years

communications.subject: Nevada Public Records Act Request: New construction permits in the last 2 years
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records sufficient to show all new construction permits issued by the Nevada EPA for Washoe, Storey, and Lyon counties in the period from 2022 - present, including but not limited to facility ID, applicant, address, date of application, date of issue/approval, and type of facility. Please provide this in a tabular format such as a CSV or Excel file.
